    "created_at": "2016-10-21T10:13:22Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-10-21T10:13:22Z",
    "body": "@PinkyJie Just an idea here but environment variables are normally inherited from their parent shell. On macOS the path is sourced in your `.bashrc` (I believe) so when you launch your app in development from the command line the environment variable is inherited.  In production you launch it as an application and thus has no shell environment to inherit.\n"
  },
